        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=36618&amp;TOPIC_ID=4647&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Alan+quoted+on+interrealm+shammy+board+re+npc+spel&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/ubb/everquest/Forum1/HTML/000601.html" target="_blank">http://boards.station.sony.com/ubb/everquest/Forum1/HTML/000601.html</a></P><P>Obviously the recent change to the way NPCs choose their spells has been receiving some attention from players. I think it’s one of the best changes we’ve seen in a while (sure, I like the pet thing too  ).<BR>I just wanted to pop in and let you all know that the intent of these changes is to make things a little more… (I would normally use the word “realistic” here, but that usually causes me trouble…) internally consistent. Basically, the tuning stopped when the NPCs were picking spells that were similar to those that PCs pick.</P><P>But the spell selections aren’t the only things we’re changing.</P><P>For example, and I didn’t even know this happened, Enchanter NPCs used to get an automatic chance to hit with their spells, regardless of the resistances of their target. We took that ability away from them. Now if they want to have a better chance to land spells they are going to have to cast a Tash spell.</P><P>The goal here is to make things fairer when it comes to NPC spell casters, and it applies to both sides.</P><P>We hope to be examining other aspects of this whole fairness thing as time goes on.</P><P>Alan</P><P>xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx</P><P><BR><a href="www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=235322" target="_blank">Zetapsi Kappaphi</a> - 54 Dark-elf (always minus the elf) Necromonster <BR>The Watchmen... of Karana<BR>(click name for Magelo profile)<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
